<Layout title="About - BookTrails" description="Learn about BookTrails - aggregating authentic book mentions from thoughtful voices across podcasts, interviews, and conversations.">
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-light text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-8">About</h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
        <div class="text-lg text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            There's no shortage of sites for book recommendations. A cursory Google search throws up thousands of results. Though I've long been tempted to build a site to aggregate book lists and recommendations, I've so far avoided the temptation.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            However, I was listening to some podcasts and the guests mentioned some books and had interesting things—both good and bad—to say about them. That's when the idea hit me that it's probably a better idea to aggregate mentions of books by smart and thoughtful people, and that's how this humble little site was born.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            What I do is make a note of book mentions I come across and update them here with some context. That's it. Nothing more.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-700">
